Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Spray four 2-cup ramekins with cooking spray. Tear croissants into large pieces and place 1 torn croissant in each ramekin. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper in medium bowl. Ladle half of egg mixture over croissants. Evenly sprinkle ham, broccoli and cheese over croissants. Ladle remaining egg mixture into ramekins. Bake 20 minutes or until puffed and center is set. (Pull aside a piece of croissant in the center to check.)